Let \Sigma, the r.e. subobject classifier, be the closure of the decidable truth values 2 = { \mathopen {} \left \{ \top , \bot \right \} \mathclose {}} under countable joins; that is,
\Sigma = { \mathopen {} \left \{ p \in \Omega \mid \exists f \in 2 ^{ \mathbb {N} } . \ p \leftrightarrow { \mathopen {} \left ( \exists n.f { \mathopen {} \left ( n \right ) \mathclose {}} = \top \right ) \mathclose {}} \right \} \mathclose {}}
It's clearly a sublattice of \Omega. Observe that by Markov's Principle, the truth-values in \Sigma are \lnot \lnot-closed; i.e. \forall p \in \Omega . \lnot \lnot { \mathopen {} \left ( p \in \Sigma \right ) \mathclose {}} \to p \in \Sigma So \Sigma \rightarrowtail \nabla2.
